    "Classification accuracy was determined at three levels of minimal detection confidence: 0.80, 0.85, and 0.90.",
    "The maximum detection accuracy was achieved at the 0.90 level of minimum detection confidence, which is greater than 85%.",
    "Kumar et al. (2023) 3.",
    "Apple, valsa canker Branches Disease detection DC-CNN models were created using several spectral pre-processing algorithms.",
    "The models' classification mechanism was visualized using the gradientweighted class activation mapping (Grad-CAM) approach with saliency maps and gradient histograms."
